note
; @pos 125 -69
; @stop 2 10 left

; MOD is a classic tracker music format
; from the Amiga era.
; Tracker music is written as rows of events.
; Each row encodes what to do next, 
; such as which audio sample to play, 
; at what pitch, and which effect to apply.
noteEnd

note
; @pos 171 12
; @stop 5 5
; These four horizontal lanes are the four
; playback channels of the MOD.
noteEnd

note
; @pos 265 58
; @stop 6 5
; Each channel reads row data, 
; selects a sample, sets pitch and volume,
; and produces one signal.
noteEnd

note
; @pos 347 -10
;                                  .
; The samples are selected by  ....;;.  
; the sample player based on   ::::;;;;.
; the sample number extracted  ::::;;:'
; from the active row.             :'

; @stop 11 5 left
noteEnd

note
; @pos 392 -38
